content: You have entered a circular map. In the following questions, I will tell you what items are on the map, as well as your position and movements. Note that your answer should include only the name of the item and no other words.(Notice that for the same ring map, if the clockwise and counterclockwise paths in the route are exchanged, it will be possible to return to the starting point from the endpoint.)

Moving in a clockwise direction from the cassette, the elements on the path are an Australian Silky Terrier, a bra, an analog clock, a ground beetle, a Border Terrier, a valley, an English Springer Spaniel, a harvestman, and an earth star. Starting from the valley, you move around the ring by 3 steps in a clockwise direction, and you move around the ring by 10 steps in a counter-clockwise direction. What will you find?
